4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possibility as the paper deals with notions of equivalence and saturation in neighbourhood structures, which are mathematical concepts. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper deals with semantic tools used in reasoning about non-normal modal logics, which has applications in programming language semantics.
